## What "presentation-ready" means

### Asterisk
- [ ] Zero stale imports (no `origami/workspace` references)
- [ ] Clean `go vet ./...`, `go build ./...`, `go test ./...`
- [ ] README tells the story: problem, solution, results (M19 numbers)
- [ ] `asterisk calibrate` demo runs cleanly with meaningful output
- [ ] Ground truth dataset is JSON (reviewable), not just Go structs

### Origami
- [ ] `examples/playground/` runs and demonstrates all concepts
- [ ] API surface is stable — no breaking changes pending
- [ ] `docs/framework-guide.md` is current and coherent
- [ ] Test coverage on public API is solid
- [ ] README positions Origami as a standalone framework

